Package se.arkalix.descriptor

Class InterfaceDescriptor

  • java.lang.Object
    • se.arkalix.descriptor.InterfaceDescriptor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<InterfaceDescriptor>
    public final class InterfaceDescriptor
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<InterfaceDescriptor>
    Names a network interface protocol triplet.

    Each provided Arrowhead service exposes its functionality via at least one interface. An interface consists of a transport protocol, a requirement to either use or not to use TLS/DTLS, as well as a payload encoding. When it is advertised what interfaces a certain service support, each of those interfaces will be represented by an instance of this descriptor.

      • valueOf

        public static InterfaceDescriptor valueOf​(java.lang.String triplet)
        Parses given string into interface triplet.

        Valid strings must match the following regular expression: 

         ([0-9A-Z_]+)-(IN)?SECURE-([0-9A-Z_]+)
        Parameters:
        triplet - String to parse.
        Returns:
        Cached or new interface triplet.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If triplet is malformed.
